{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"08c2bf61-c156-4f22-a185-f0a2d24c5990","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2 / .NET 9**, so you can use the modern constructor-injection pattern. Here's the recommended approach:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests : IAsyncDisposable\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private readonly MyService _service;\n    private HttpClient? _client;\n\n    // Sync init + TestContext injection via constructor\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        _service = new MyService();\n    }\n\n    // Async init — runs before each test\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        _client = await _service.CreateClientAsync();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task MyTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test...\");\n        // ...\n    }\n\n    // Async cleanup\n    public async ValueTask DisposeAsync()\n    {\n        if (_client is not null)\n            await _client.DisposeAsync();\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points (MSTest 3+):**\n\n- **`TestContext`** — inject via constructor, not the legacy static property setter.\n- **Sync init** — use the constructor directly.\n- **Async init** — use `[TestInitialize] async Task` (runs per-test).\n- **Cleanup** — implement `IAsyncDisposable` or `IDisposable`, or use `[TestCleanup]`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c89c39d9-4735-4964-90d3-04bd24254577","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 with .NET 9.0. This is a modern version of MSTest (v3+). Let me provide the recommended approach.\n\nIn MSTest v3+, the recommended way is:\n\n1. **TestContext injection**: Use constructor injection (`TestContext` as a constructor parameter) — the old static property pattern is legacy.\n2. **Synchronous init**: Use the constructor.\n3. **Asynchronous init**: Use `[TestInitialize]` with an async method, or implement `IAsyncDisposable`/`IDisposable` for cleanup.\n\nActually, let me think more carefully. In MSTest 3.x:\n\n\n- `TestContext` gets injected through the constructor, which is the modern approach\n- Synchronous initialization happens in the constructor itself\n- Asynchronous initialization uses `[TestInitialize]` as an async method, with cleanup handled via `[TestCleanup]`, `IDisposable`, or `IAsyncDisposable`","outputTokens":646,"requestId":"67D7:226394:2C4EC6F:30F3C8B:69FD3F24"},"id":"4c192429-4a59-4b14-9a57-b88b92251ae8","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:41:40.056Z","parentId":"d67ca38b-b916-478f-b2ff-5c3cdc299674"}
